   "source": [
    "# Ice sheet model simulations of the Antarctic Ice Sheet over the last two glacial cycles \n",
    "\n",
    "(c) 2020 by Torsten Albrecht (torsten.albrecht@pik-potsdam.de) | Potsdam Institute for Climate Impact Research (PIK)\n",
    "\n",
    "This example loads and plots results from Torsten Albrecht's ensemble simulations of Antarctica. \n",
    "\n",
    "**data:** Albrecht, Torsten (2019): PISM parameter ensemble analysis of Antarctic Ice Sheet glacial cycle simulations. PANGAEA, https://doi.pangaea.de/10.1594/PANGAEA.909728\n",
    "\n",
    "More details on the ensemble can be found [here](https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3585118)."
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "through-maria",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Lazily load the model data\n",
    "Selected outputs from the model ensemble are stored in two zarr directories in the google cloud. The data are cataloged in intake catalogs to simplify loading. \n",
    "\n",
    "present contains fields that describe the state of each ensemble member at the end of the simulation - present-day.\n",
    "\n",
    "mask_score_time_series contains time series of an integer mask (indicating ice-free/grounded/floating/ocean) and ensemble member score"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "august-penetration",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2021-06-02T21:17:25.678327Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2021-06-02T21:17:25.677714Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2021-06-02T21:17:30.608804Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2021-06-02T21:17:30.608121Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# load the intake catalog\n",
    "cat = intake.open_catalog('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ldeo-glaciology/pangeo-pismpaleo/main/paleopism.yaml')\n",
    "\n",
    "# load each of the zarr diretories contained in the intake catalog\n",
    "present  = cat[\"present\"].to_dask()\n",
    "mask_score_time_series  = cat[\"mask_score_time_series\"].to_dask()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "boring-berkeley",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. take a look at the resulting xarrays\n",
    "\n",
    "### present is a 7-dimensional xarray:\n",
    "\n",
    "It has dimensions corresponding to each of the four ensemble parameters:\n",
    "            par_esia, par_ppq, par_prec and par_visc\n",
    "            \n",
    "It has one time dimension, but this is only one element long so it can be mostly ignored.\n",
    "\n",
    "It haas two spatial dimensions, x and y."
   ]
  },
